<sect1>NAME 
 <P>vutil - venus utility program



<sect1>SYNOPSIS<P>
<bf>vutil</bf> &lsqb;-cop COP modes&rsqb; &lsqb; -cs &rsqb; 
    &lsqb;-d debug level&rsqb; &lsqb;-mc 0 | 1 &rsqb; &lsqb;-p 0 | 1&rsqb;
<P> &lsqb;-shutdown&rsqb; &lsqb;-stats&rsqb; &lsqb;-swap&rsqb;
<P>


<sect1>DESCRIPTION<P>
<bf>vutil</bf> dynamically alters various parameters on a running Venus.  It
reads the value of the file /usr/coda/venus.cache/pid and sends signals to
that process.

The parameters are:
<descrip>
<tag><bf>-cop</bf> <em>COP modes</em></tag> Controls what Coda Optimistic
Protocol (COP) options are enabled.  <em>COP modes</em> is interpreted
according to the following bit-mask: &lsqb;PIGGYCOP2 | ASYNCCOP2 | ASYNCCOP1
&rsqb;.  Only some combinations are legal.
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>-cs</bf></tag> Clears internal counters used in statistics reporting.
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>-d</bf> <em>debug level</em></tag> Sets the debug level to <em>debug
level</em>.  Meaningful values are &lcub;0, 1, 10, 100, 1000&rcub;.
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>-mc</bf> <em>0 | 1</em></tag> Enable/disables multicast 
(0 = ``OFF,'' 1 = ``ON'')
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>-p</bf> <em>0 | 1</em></tag> Enables/disables profiling 
(0 = ``OFF,'' 1 = ``ON'')
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>-shutdown</bf></tag> Shuts Venus down gracefully.
<P></descrip>

<descrip>

<tag><bf>-stats</bf></tag> Causes Venus to dump internal counters and other
statistics to its log file.
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>-swap</bf></tag> Causes Venus to move its current log
file to &lt;log-file&gt;.old and reinitialize &lt;log-file&gt;.
<P></descrip>


<sect1>DIAGNOSTICS<P>
Only the super user can run <bf>vutil</bf>.


<sect1>FILES<P>
<em>/usr/coda/venus.cache/pid</em>

<em>/usr/coda/venus.cahe/venus.log</em>



<sect1>BUGS<P>
Venus cache directory is assumed to be <em>/usr/coda/venus.cache</em>.



